@josephdillon9698 It was always just a flu or a cold. I got it 4 times according to doctors, just a sniffle. 'You're body temperature is high and you have a fever!!!'' yeah the flu tends to do that. What's that? It kills the elderly and young who have weaker immune systems and lack of anti-bodies. The flu has never been that specific before! To think it kills the weaker immune systems and bounces off the other. Madness. No virus or bacteria has ever done this! Let's lock the economy down.

What is funny or maybe not, is people who died in traffic collisions were also counted towards the death toll because they had a virus and bacteria in their systems. Everyone has a virus in their system, if you got a TB jab as a kid - you carry that virus too. So numbers were always false.

Remember Swine Flu outbreak? I could have almost turned into a pig like Spirted Away! Derp.
